:: Public Holidays
"Nyårsdagen"                  public on january 1
"Trettondedag jul"            public religious on january 6
"Långfredagen"                public religious on easter minus 2
"Påskdagen"                   public religious on easter
"Annandag påsk"               public religious on easter plus 1
"Första maj"                  public on may 1
"Kristi himmelsfärdsdag"      public religious on easter plus 39 days
"Svenska flaggans dag"        civil on ((year < 2005) ? [june 6] : noop)
"Nationaldagen"               public on ((year >= 2005) ? [june 6] : noop)
"Pingstdagen"                 public religious on easter plus 49 days
"Midsommardagen"              public on saturday before june 26
"Alla helgons dag"            public religious on first sunday in november minus 1
"Juldagen"                    public religious on december 25
"Annandag jul"                public religious on december 26

:: Religious
"Trettondagsafton"            religious on january 5
"Kyndelsmässodagen"           religious on february 2
"Fettisdagen"                 religious on easter minus 47 days
"Askonsdagen"                 religious on easter minus 46 days
"Skärtorsdagen"               religious on easter minus 3
"Påskafton"                   religious on easter minus 1
"Valborgsmässoafton"          religious on april 30
"Pingstafton"                 religious on easter plus 48 days
"Annandag pingst"             public religious on ((year < 2005) ? ([easter] + 50 days) : noop)
"Annandag pingst"             religious on ((year >= 2005) ? ([easter] + 50 days) : noop)
::"Annandag pingst"             religious on easter plus 50 days
"Allhelgonaafton"             religious on friday before november 5
"Allhelgonadagen"             religious on november 1
"Första advent"               religious on sunday before december 24 minus 21 days
"Andra advent"                religious on sunday before december 24 minus 14 days
"Lucia"                       religious on december 13
"Tredje advent"               religious on sunday before december 24 minus 7 days
"Fjärde advent"               religious on sunday before december 24
"Julafton"                    religious on december 24
"Menlösa barns dag"           religious on ((year < 2000) ? [december 28] : noop)
"Värnlösa barns dag"          religious on ((year >= 2000) ? [december 28] : noop)

:: Cultural
"Förintelsens minnesdag"      commemorative on ((year >= 1999) ? [january 27] : noop)
"Alla hjärtans dag"           cultural on february 14
"Internationella kvinnodagen" cultural on march 8
"Våffeldagen"                 cultural on march 25
"Mors dag"                    cultural on last sunday in may
